Kenya on Saturday recorded 13 new cases of Covid-19 from a sample of 2,342 collected in the last 24 hours. The positivity rate is at 0.6 per cent. In a statement released by Health CS Mutahi Kagwe, from the cases, 9 are Kenyans while 4 are foreigners. Eight are males and five are females. The youngest patient is a 5-year old while the oldest is 87 years old. This brings the total number of confirmed positive cases to 323,773 out of a cumulative of 3,598,809. In terms of County distribution; Nairobi recorded 10 cases, and Uasin Gishu 3. The number of recovered patients in the last 24 hours is 28, 27 of them were in the Home-Based Care and Isolation Program while one is from a health facility in the country. The total recoveries are now at 317,960, out of which 264,932 were in Home-Based Care and Isolation while 53,028 were in health facilities countrywide. There were no deaths recorded. The cumulative number of deaths remains at 5,649. There is no patient admitted to the Intensive Care Unit (ICU) or in the High Dependency Unit (HDU). A total of 2 patients are currently admitted to various health facilities countrywide, while 151 are under the Home-Based Isolation and Care program. There is one patient on supplemental oxygen.